name: app.R
content:
library(shiny)
library(bslib)
library(ggplot2)
library(gridExtra)

rw_impov_grp <- read.csv("exported_fig_3_data.csv")
rw_hoggdata <- read.csv("distribution_indicators.csv")

link_gitlab <- tags$a("gitlab", href = "https://gitlab.com/aschniedermann/pandots", target = "_blank")
link_gdoc <- tags$a("googledoc", href = "https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gKOqGy08cAQfdV-0sTJy-Whdw8gEi391G0B0vWx4MKw/edit#heading=h.r67ikr567okf", target = "_blank")


 shinylive::export("C:/Users/trantor/Documents/git_projects/pandots/r_project/shinyapp", "C:/Users/trantor/Documents/git_projects/pandots-shiny/docs")

# Define UI for app that draws a histogram ----
ui <- page_navbar(
  title = "PanDots",
  bg = "black",
  
  nav_panel(
    "Introduction",
    card_header("Introduction"),
    full_screen = TRUE,
    p("Put intro .md here...")
  ),
  
  nav_panel(
    "Production",
    card_header("Plot (citing x cited)"),
    full_screen = TRUE,
    p("The production of different research items during the pandemic...")
  ),
  
  nav_panel(
    "Evidence base",
    card_header("Distribution Dynamics"),
    full_screen = TRUE,
    sidebarLayout(
      #fillable = TRUE,
      sidebarPanel(
        selectInput("cxc_citingcorona",
                    "Citing item has corona:",
                    unique(as.character(rw_impov_grp$citingcorona))
        ),
        
        selectInput("cxc_citedcorona",
                    "Cited item has corona:",
                    unique(as.character(rw_impov_grp$citedcorona))
        ),
        
        selectInput("dist_articletype",
                    "Document type group:",
                    unique(as.character(rw_hoggdata$cited_type))
        ),
        
        selectInput("citing_date",
                    "Pandemic Month:",
                    unique(as.character(rw_impov_grp$citing_date))
        ),
        
        br(),
        
        sliderInput("cxc_plotwindow",
                    "plotrange in months:",
                    min = min(rw_impov_grp$citing_date),
                    max = max(rw_impov_grp$citing_date),
                    value = c(0,median(rw_impov_grp$citing_date)),
                    step = 1
        ), 
        width = 2
      ),
      mainPanel(
        plotOutput("plot_cc"), plotOutput("ds_plots"),DT::dataTableOutput("table"),
        width = 10
      )
    ), 
  ),
  
  nav_menu(
    title = "Links",
    align = "right",
    nav_item(link_gitlab),
    nav_item(link_gdoc)
  )
)




server <- function(input, output) {
  
  
  
  # Filter data based on selections
  output$table <- DT::renderDataTable(DT::datatable({
    data <- rw_impov_grp
    if (input$citing_date != "All") {
      data <- data[data$citing_date == input$citing_date,]
    }
    if (input$cxc_citedcorona != "All") {
      data <- data[data$citedcorona == input$cxc_citedcorona,]
    }
    if (input$cxc_citingcorona != "All") {
      data <- data[data$citingcorona == input$cxc_citingcorona,]
    }
    data
  }))
  
  
  output$plot_cc <- renderPlot(
    ggplot(rw_impov_grp[rw_impov_grp$citedcorona == input$cxc_citedcorona & rw_impov_grp$citingcorona == input$cxc_citingcorona,],
           aes(x=citing_date, y=percent, label=cited_type_agg)) +
      geom_line(aes(linetype = cited_type_agg, color = input$cxc_citedcorona), size = 1) +
      geom_line(aes(x=citing_date, y=unique_rate), size = 0.6, color = "gray") +
      geom_col(aes(x=citing_date, y=monthlytruerefrate), position="dodge" ,size=1, fill="gray", color=NA, alpha=.05) + 
      geom_label(aes(label = label, color = input$cxc_citedcorona), label.size = 0, alpha = 0.8) +
      scale_y_continuous(breaks=seq(0, 1, by = 0.2), minor_breaks =seq(0, 1, by = 0.1)) +
      scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2], by = 3), minor_breaks =seq(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2], by = 1),limits=c(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2])) +
      xlab("Pandemic month (from January 2020)") +
      ylab("Proportion") +
      labs(caption="Source: OpenAlex | PubMed (document types)") +
      theme_minimal() + 
      guides(label = "none", linetype = "none", color=guide_legend(title="Corona relatedness of References")) +
      theme(legend.position = "bottom")
  )
  
  ds_hoggplot_kurtosis <- reactive(
    ggplot(rw_hoggdata[rw_hoggdata$citedcorona == input$cxc_citedcorona & rw_hoggdata$citingcorona == input$cxc_citingcorona & rw_hoggdata$cited_type == input$dist_articletype,]) +
      geom_line(aes(x=citing_date, y=hogg_kurtosis), size = 1) +
      scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2], by = 3), minor_breaks =seq(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2], by = 1),limits=c(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2])) +
      xlab("Pandemic month (from January 2020)") +      
      ylab("Kurtosis") +
      ggtitle(paste("Absolute Kurtosis of monthly citation distribution to",input$dist_articletype)) +     
      theme_minimal() + 
      guides(label = "none", linetype = "none", color=guide_legend(title="type")) +
      theme(legend.position = "bottom")
  )
  
  ds_hoggplot_skewness <- reactive(
    ggplot(rw_hoggdata[rw_hoggdata$citedcorona == input$cxc_citedcorona & rw_hoggdata$citingcorona == input$cxc_citingcorona & rw_hoggdata$cited_type == input$dist_articletype,]) +
      geom_line(aes(x=citing_date, y=hogg_skewness), size = 1) +
      scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2], by = 3), minor_breaks =seq(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2], by = 1),limits=c(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2])) +
      xlab("Pandemic month (from January 2020)") +      
      ylab("Skewness") +
      ggtitle(paste("Absolute Skewness of monthly citation distribution to",input$dist_articletype)) +     
      theme_minimal() + 
      guides(label = "none", linetype = "none", color=guide_legend(title="type")) +
      theme(legend.position = "bottom")
  )
  
  ds_hhi_plot <- reactive(
    ggplot(rw_hoggdata[rw_hoggdata$citedcorona == input$cxc_citedcorona & rw_hoggdata$citingcorona == input$cxc_citingcorona & rw_hoggdata$cited_type == input$dist_articletype,]) +
      geom_line(aes(x=citing_date, y=herfindahl_relative), size = 1) +
      scale_x_continuous(breaks=seq(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2], by = 3), minor_breaks =seq(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2], by = 1),limits=c(input$cxc_plotwindow[1], input$cxc_plotwindow[2])) +
      xlab("Pandemic month (from January 2020)") +      
      ylab("Portion of maximum HHI (in %)") +
      ggtitle(paste("Concentration of citations to",input$dist_articletype), "(as portion of maximum Herfindal-Hirschman index)") +
      theme_minimal() + 
      guides(label = "none", linetype = "none", color=guide_legend(title="type")) +
      theme(legend.position = "bottom")
  )
  
  output$ds_plots <- renderPlot({
    ptlist <- list(ds_hoggplot_skewness(),ds_hoggplot_kurtosis(), ds_hhi_plot())
    grid.arrange(grobs=ptlist, ncol=length(ptlist))
  })
  
  
  
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
